<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOVIES TO TAPE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Radio Days (Channel 13 Sunday at 8 p.m.): Growing up in Brooklyn, dreaming of 
Manhattan, heroes and heroines of the radio. Another wonderful Woody Allen 
fantasy-reminiscence. (2:00) 
</P>
<P>
Blowup (TMC Sunday at 2:45 a.m.; Wednesday at 6 p.m.): Michelangelo Antonioni's 
contemporary classic: murder, malaise and photography in swinging London. 
(1:51) 
</P>
<P>
Mephisto (A&amp;E Tuesday at 6 &amp; 10 p.m.): Istvan Szabo's 1981 
Oscar-winner: a vibrant portrait of an opportunist actor (Klaus Maria 
Brandauer) in Nazi Germany, based on Klaus Mann's novel. (2:15) 
</P>
<P>
Victor/Victoria (Channel 5 Wednesday at 7:30 p.m.): Julie Andrews as a 
chanteuse in a chaos of cross-dressing in 1930s Paris: prime Blake Edwards' 
comedy from a 1933 German original. (2:30) 
</P>
<P>
Hour of the Star (Channel 28 Saturday at 10 p.m.): The story of a plain Sao 
Paolo typist who dreams of glamour, made into a powerful portrait of the urban 
underclass by Suzana Amaral. (2:00) 
</P>
