<HEADLINE>
<P>
ON THE COVER: THESE ARE "TRYING TIMES" FOR KCET. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The comedy anthology series, whose humorous stories deal with contemporary 
angst, returns to the local PBS station for its second season Sunday at 8 p.m. 
on Channel 28. 
</P>
<P>
In "Hunger Chic," Carrie Fisher and Griffin Dunne play a self-centered pair of 
yuppies coping with a strange series of incidents brought about by an unusual 
maid (Danitra Vance, formerly of "Saturday Night Live"). 
</P>
<P>
Next Sunday's installment casts Geena Davis as a seductive spy in "The Hit 
List." On Nov. 12, Jean Stapleton plays the put-upon employee of tyrannnical 
Corey Feldman in "The Boss." 
</P>
<P>
New half-hour episodes of "Trying Times" will be followed at 8:30 p.m. Sunday 
by repeats from last season. The stories also can be seen from 10 to 11 p.m. on 
Tuesdays. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, COLOR, (cover) 'Trying Times' BACK FOR A SECOND TIME: KCET's Comedy 
Anthology Returns With Geena Davis, Jean Stapleton, Corey Feldman, Griffin 
Dunne, Carrie Fisher, Danitra Vance 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
