<TEXT>
<P>
HOT TYPE: Every magazine is entitled to have an anniversary issue, even RIP, 
which celebrates its third anniversary this month. The new December issue of 
the sassy hard-rock bible features a Motley Crue pull-out poster, Serious Rock 
Talk with Jon Bon Jovi ("Q: What would you do if you could be invisible for a 
day? A: Hang out in a girls' shower. A girls' shower in the locker-room of a 
strip club."), features on Metallica, L.A. Guns, Warrant &amp; Tora Tora and 
gloriously frank reader mail ("Your cover story on Great White left me feeling 
nothing but disgust for the entire band . . . if the only angle they want to 
promote is how accessible they are to horny groupies, a sign in the window of 
the tour bus would suffice"). . . . And KRS-One, who's out on a 27-city tour 
with L.A.'s own Young MC, isn't just doing rap concerts this fall. Both 
performers will be giving a series of lectures at local colleges along the way, 
in part as a way of encouraging students to join the teaching profession. So 
far the duo's lecture schedule includes such lofty institutions as Princeton 
and Yale. 
</P>
