<HEADLINE>
<P>
JONES' OLDIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It was interesting to come across Calendar's Oct. 8 article on Rickie Lee 
Jones. I'm a retiree and was totally unaware of her talent until I heard her on 
TV doing the old Eddie Cantor song, "Making Whoopee." 
</P>
<P>
So I went to record stores on Florida's Gulf Coast trying to find tapes of her 
doing music of the '20s and '30s. Clerks remarked that many older people were 
asking for the same thing. 
</P>
<P>
Jones is missing a market if she doesn't do more of the '20s and '30s with her 
cute voice. 
</P>
<P>
DICK GRUMBLATT 
</P>
<P>
Venice, Fla. 
</P>
</TEXT>
