<HEADLINE>
<P>
BIG BEAT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Claudia Puig's puff piece, "Music to Someone's Ears," details how demographics 
were molded to make a case for dumping the classic KFAC. Given the bottom-line, 
throwaway mentality at work here, it sounds more like a dismal demonstration of 
demonographics. 
</P>
<P>
As if the air in Los Angeles isn't bad enough already, the Texas-based 
Evergreen Corp. is now pouring its noxious audio fumes into our cultural 
atmosphere. 
</P>
<P>
Let's hope the grandiose pipe dreams of those who now own and run KKBT lead to 
their speedy demise in a medium already up to its ears in noisome offal. It 
would serve these carpetbaggers right. 
</P>
<P>
ED JAMES 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
