<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEW BOOKS: SWEATERS BY HAND: DESIGNS FOR SPINNERS AND KNITTERS BY HELENE RUSH 
AND RACHAEL EMMONS, (INTERWEAVE PRESS; 1988) 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Judith Sims 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RACHAEL EMMONS IS a spinner who knits, Helene Rush knits and is learning to 
spin, and together these two Portland, Me., women have created a beautiful and 
useful book -- even for those who don't spin their own yarns. Each sweater 
design (some simple, some lush, using all kinds of yarns from silk and mohair 
to sturdy wool) comes with spinning, dyeing and knitting instructions, complete 
with suggestions for modifications. Because hand-spun yarns don't always 
conform to commercial yarn weights, the authors give commercial equivalents for 
those of us who don't spin. But here is fair warning: After absorbing this 
book, I'm seriously considering buying a spinning wheel. Of course, the sofa 
will have to go. ($17.95) Judith Sims 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Drawing, 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
<TYPE>
<P>
