<P>
BANGLADESH SHANTYTOWN FIRE KILLS 8; 1,000 HOMELESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DHAKA, Bangladesh 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fire swept through a shantytown Friday, killing eight people, destroying 200 
houses and leaving 1,000 people homeless, officials said. Authorities blamed 
arsonists. 
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said the blaze was started by students from a nearby college who 
poured gasoline on the mud-and-straw huts. 
</P>
