<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGHLIGHTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FLASH FROM THE PAST: Sally Rand, who gained notoriety for her performance of 
the exotic fan dance at the 1933 Chicago World's Fair, lived in Glendora most 
of her adult life. She bought property there in the 1920s and lived there until 
she died in 1979 at the age of 75. 
</P>
