106 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLICE CALLS FOR DOMESTIC THREATS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Yocum is both right and wrong. She is right in saying that battered persons 
should leave the abuser and prosecute him (or her) to the fullest. She is 
right: Courts should punish abusers quickly and severely. But, Yocum is wrong 
about police not being able to respond to a call like Maria's. If Maria's 
father had been a county supervisor, or a movie star, or a police officer 
wouldn't they have come? And, isn't a life more important than a drug bust or a 
robbery -- even one in progress? 
</P>
<P>
Maybe the ultimate answer is one women must make themselves: Stop getting 
linked-up with brutal, immature men. 
</P>
<P>
JOYCE CAWLEY 
</P>
<P>
South Laguna 
</P>
</TEXT>
