<HEADLINE>
<P>
JUVENILE JUSTICE NOMINEE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By from Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
President Bush will nominate Robert W. Sweet Jr. as administrator of the Office 
of Juvenile Justice and Delinquency Prevention, the White House announced last 
week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA101589-0097 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 120843 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
October 15, 1989, Sunday, Bulldog Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
