<HEADLINE>
<P>
GUIDE TO REPAIRS FOR DO-IT-YOURSELF OWNERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The homeowner confronted by minor repairs might get some help from a book 
designed for beginning do-it-yourselfers. 
</P>
<P>
"Small Home Repairs Made Easy," an 88-page manual, is edited by Robert L. 
Berko, executive director of the nonprofit Consumer Education Research Center. 
</P>
<P>
The illustrated paperback lists step-by-step directions on how to do 
around-the-house repairs. According to Berko, such mysteries as unstopping the 
toilet, fixing the doorbell and repairing the garage door are within the 
capability of even the most unskilled. 
</P>
<P>
The book can be ordered for $6.50, including postage, from the Consumer 
Education Research Center, 350 Scotland Road, Orange, N.J. 07050, or by calling 
(800) 872-0121. 
</P>
</TEXT>
