<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE: CIVIL ENGINEERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LINDA MARTINI-POSNER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Psomas &amp; Associates has appointed Robert S. Roscoe as project manager. 
Based in Sacramento, Roscoe will be responsible for projects in the water, 
waste water and municipal services sector. The company also maintains offices 
in Santa Monica, Costa Mesa and Riverside. 
</P>
<P>
Law Firms 
</P>
<P>
Catherine R. Reuter has joined Pircher, Nichols &amp; Meeks in Century City as 
an associate attorney involved in directing land use planning and developments. 
Reuter was recently elected to the board of directors of the Los Angeles 
Central City Assn. 
</P>
<P>
Brokers 
</P>
<P>
Mark A. Piscitelli has been named senior vice president and district manager of 
Grubb &amp; Ellis Co.'s Inland Empire offices. Working out of the Ontario 
office, Piscitelli will oversee the management of 45 sales and leasing brokers 
specializing in office, industrial and retail properties in San Bernardino and 
Riverside counties. 
</P>
<P>
The Prudential Real Estate Affiliates Inc. has made two announcements: Karun 
Khanna has been named vice president, director of lender services, and Jon 
Hubbell has become assistant general counsel. Khanna will be in charge of 
business and product development of CLOS (Computerized Loan Origination 
System). Both Khanna and Hubbell will be based at the firm's national 
headquarters in Costa Mesa. 
</P>
<P>
ACCOLADES: Robert A. Crane, founder and president of Crane/Sachar Realty 
Management Co. has been appointed to the board of governors of the American 
Society of Real Estate Counselors for a three-year term. The international 
organization serves public and private owners, investors and developers as a 
source of knowledge. It also establishes professional standards. 
</P>
<P>
Marketing Firms 
</P>
<P>
Richard N. Jaffee has joined Martin Advertising &amp; Public Relations in 
Tustin as vice president. He will form a separate division with an emphasis on 
commercial real estate and financial services. 
</P>
<P>
Information Services 
</P>
<P>
San Diego-headquartered Dataquick Information Systems has appointed James W. 
Eubanks vice president of financial services. Eubanks will operate from the 
Orange County office, but will be responsible for corporate-wide activities 
among the financial services industries of California and Arizona. The company 
provides a computerized real estate information service. 
</P>
<P>
Mortgage Firms 
</P>
<P>
Based in Costa Mesa, Bayport Mortgage Corp., a subsidiary of Warmington 
companies, has named Laura C. Guilline director of mortgage finance. Guilline 
comes to the firm from Far West Savings &amp; Loan Assn., where she was vice 
president, regional manager for wholesale lending. 
</P>
<P>
Architects 
</P>
<P>
The Nadel Partnership Inc. in Los Angeles has a new partner: Robert Jacques. He 
has been responsible for the design of office, mixed-use, industrial, retail 
and residential projects, including the master planning of a 50-acre office 
park. 
</P>
<P>
George Williamson has been promoted to vice president of planning at the 
Lightfoot Planning Group. He will also manage its new office in Rancho 
California, which will provide planning, design and landscape architecture 
services in Riverside County. 
</P>
<P>
Ragnar C. Quale &amp; Associates has appointed Paul Anders Quale director. He 
has been the project architect for the recently completed Los Angeles Temporary 
Central Library. The firm's office is located in downtown Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
Two staff changes have been made at Los Angeles-based Albert C. Martin &amp; 
Associates: Ron Fink has been named principal designer and will direct one of 
four design studios; and Jon Ziegler has been made director of civil 
engineering, responsible for the overall management of the firm's engineering 
projects. 
</P>
<P>
The Community Redevelopment Agency of Los Angeles has appointed Steven 
Valenzuela project manager of the Bunker Hill redevelopment project, the 
agency's centerpiece of its revitalization efforts in the downtown area. 
</P>
<P>
Altoon &amp; Porter Architects has named three new associates: Randolph C. 
Larsen, Hendra Kusuma and James H. Hansen. Larsen's responsibilities will 
include handling construction documents and administration phases of major 
projects. Kusuma will oversee CADD Systems research, development and management 
for the architectural services of the entire practice, and Hansen will be 
responsible for master planning, architectural design and development and 
specific project management. LINDA MARTINI-POSNER 
</P>
</TEXT>
