CALIFORNIA: IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
SACRAMENTO; 
</P>
<P>
SUSPECT IN SLAYING OF GIRL, 6, SURRENDERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Sacramento man whom police sought in the drive-by killing of a 6-year-old 
girl has turned himself in, authorities said. James Montanez, 27, walked with 
his lawyer into the Hall of Justice. He was booked into the county jail on a 
charge of first-degree murder and held without bail until arraignment next 
week. Leticia Gonzales was killed and her mother, Esperanza Gonzales, 24, and 
aunt, Katrina Richards, 27, were wounded Tuesday night when gunfire was sprayed 
from a car into a group of people standing at Northgate Park. The women were 
talking with two men, known to be gang members, who police believe were the 
real targets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
