<HEADLINE>
<P>
BIG WEST ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
FRESNO STATE NOTCHES 13TH STRAIGHT VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Myron Jones ran for two touchdowns and Aaron Craver rushed for 101 yards as 
Fresno State ran away from Utah State, 34-7, in a Big West Conference game 
Saturday at Logan, Utah. 
</P>
<P>
Steven Shelley also caught five passes for 132 yards as the Bulldogs improved 
to 6-0, 3-0 in the conference. 
</P>
<P>
The Bulldogs' 13-game winning streak is the longest in school history and 
second-longest in the nation behind Notre Dame. 
</P>
<P>
The Aggies (1-5 and 1-1) played close for one quarter before Fresno State took 
control after capitalizing on three Utah State fumbles in the first half. 
</P>
<P>
Jones helped the Bulldogs draw first blood when he scored from six yards out on 
a sweep to the left side when Fresno State had a fourth-and-two with 10:24 left 
in the first quarter. 
</P>
<P>
His second touchdown, a four-yard run with 1:05 left in the first half, gave 
Fresno State a 20-7 lead. Fresno State's Steve Loop also kicked field goals of 
27 and 22 yards, both coming after Utah State fumbles. 
</P>
<P>
Tulsa 34, New Mexico St. 13 -- Dan Bitson caught two touchdown passes, one on a 
44-yard pass play in the second quarter, as the Hurricane beat the winless 
Aggies of the Big West in a nonconference game at Tulsa, Okla. 
</P>
<P>
Fullback Brett Adams picked up 123 yards in 21 carries, including a 10-yard 
touchdown run in the third quarter for Tulsa (4-3). 
</P>
<P>
David Fuess added a pair of field goals of 26 and 29 yards and tight end Bill 
Buehner scored on a 12-yard pass from quarterback T.J. Rubley for an insurance 
score in the fourth quarter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story; Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
