<HEADLINE>
<P>
PACIFIC 10 ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON MAKES MOST OF OREGON'S MISTAKES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Washington intercepted four of Bill Musgrave's passes and recovered three 
fumbles in defeating Oregon, 20-14, in a sloppily played Pacific 10 Conference 
game Saturday at Seattle. 
</P>
<P>
The Huskies took the lead for good in the third quarter on a one-yard touchdown 
run by quarterback Cary Conklin. 
</P>
<P>
The Huskies, 3-3 overall and 1-2 in the conference, avoided losing their fourth 
consecutive game, which would have been most losses in a row in Coach Don 
James' 15 seasons in Seattle. The three defeats were the most by a Washington 
team since 1976. Washington beat Oregon for the first time in three seasons. 
</P>
<P>
Washington recorded three of its seven turnovers in the fourth quarter, 
including a fumble that stopped a last-ditch Oregon drive on the Huskies' 40 
with 1:38 left. 
</P>
<P>
Oregon is now 3-3 and 2-3. 
</P>
<P>
Washington State 31, Stanford 13 -- Steve Broussard broke off tackle and ran 71 
yards for the Cougars' first touchdown early in the second quarter and scored 
again on a five-yard run later in the same period to lead No. 17 Washington 
State to a win at Pullman, Wash. 
</P>
<P>
The Cougars (6-1 and 3-1) fumbled the ball away on their first two possessions, 
but scored four touchdowns in the second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Stanford (1-5 and 1-3) led, 10-7, after scoring its only touchdown when Tom 
Vardell recovered a fumble in the end zone. 
</P>
<P>
But Aaron Garcia, who completed 23 of 41 passes for 341 yards and two 
touchdowns, hit tight end Doug Wellsandt with a 12-yard scoring pass and then 
capped a 93-yard drive with a 24-yard touchdown pass to C.J. Davis seven 
seconds before halftime and Washington State was on its way. 
</P>
<P>
Arizona St. 17, Oregon St. 17 -- Paul Justin of Arizona State threw for a pair 
of second-half touchdowns and Oregon State's Pat Chaffey ran for two scores as 
the two teams battled to a standoff at Corvallis, Ore. 
</P>
<P>
Troy Bussanich of Oregon State missed a 55-yard field-goal attempt as the game 
ended. 
</P>
<P>
Oregon State is 2-3-1 and 1-1-1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, (Southland Edition) Oregon State's Mike Maggiore (95) disrupts Arizona 
State quarterback Paul Justin, who throws incomplete pass during 17-17 tie. 
United Press International 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
