<HEADLINE>
<P>
MIKE HILL LEADS SENIORS BY 3 SHOTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ABILENE, Tex. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mike Hill birdied the final hole Saturday to take a three-shot lead after two 
rounds of the Gatlin Brothers Southwest senior tournament at Fairway Oaks 
Country Club. 
</P>
<P>
Hill shot a five-under-par 67 for a two-round total of eight-under 136, three 
shots ahead of Bruce Crampton and Butch Baird. 
</P>
<P>
Gary Player, Orville Moody, John Paul Cain, John Brodie, Jim Dent, Don 
Massengale, Walt Zembriski and Larry Ziegler are another shot back. 
</P>
<P>
Jerry Barber won the RJR tournament, the 36-hole competition for the players 
older than 60. Barber, 73, beat Charlie Sifford with a par on the second hole 
of a sudden-death playoff. 
</P>
</TEXT>
