<HEADLINE>
<P>
PATRICK WINS NEW CAR WITH ACE AT VALENCIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tom Patrick of Granada Hills scored a hole-in-one Saturday on the 185-yard 
seventh hole at Valencia Country Club in the club's third annual member-guest 
tournament and drove away with a new imported sports car. 
</P>
<P>
Patrick, 44, used a six-iron to notch his first ace in 20 years of golf. The 
ball landed in the hole on the fly, clearing the all-water approach. 
</P>
<P>
"I thought it flew the green," Patrick said. "And then we looked in the hole 
and there it was." 
</P>
</TEXT>
