<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOTHER TERESA TO LEAVE HOSPITAL AFTER A MONTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CALCUTTA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nobel Peace Prize winner Mother Teresa will soon be able return home after more 
than a month in the hospital with a heart condition, her doctors said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Mother Teresa, 79, was hospitalized Sept. 5 and fitted with a temporary 
pacemaker a few days later to help an irregular heartbeat caused by a slightly 
blocked artery. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
