<HEADLINE>
<P>
TO OUR READERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Los Angeles Times has changed several aspects of its format. The changes 
are aimed at presenting a better organized newspaper, giving easier access to 
The Times' comprehensive coverage. Among the changes: 
</P>
<P>
* Highlights, on the front of each daily section except main news, summarizes 
what is in the section. 
</P>
<P>
* The Top of Today's News on A2 briefly spotlights important news from across 
the paper. It appears Sunday through Friday. 
</P>
<P>
* Headlines, in many cases, include overview subheads that provide further 
explanation about the story. 
</P>
<P>
The Times invites readers to comment on the changes by calling 1-800-678-0105. 
Phone lines have been added to help readers get through from 7 a.m. to 8 p.m. 
daily. Or write to: "Format Changes," Los Angeles Times, Times Mirror Square, 
Los Angeles 90053. 
</P>
</TEXT>
