<HEADLINE>
<P>
DRIVER BADLY HURT, 6 OTHERS INJURED IN STREET RACE CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A driver who reportedly tried to beat a yellow light on Katella Avenue between 
the cities of Stanton and Anaheim while racing another car was seriously 
injured, and six other people received minor to moderate injuries in a two-car 
collision Saturday afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
California Highway Patrol officials said the driver of the car that ran the 
light, Cecil G. Wilson, 59, of Anaheim, was taken to UCI Medical Center in 
Orange, where he was listed in serious condition. Although an investigation is 
pending, CHP officials released a statement that Wilson had been drinking 
before the incident. 
</P>
<P>
CHP officials said Wilson had been racing against a red Porsche eastbound on 
Katella Avenue just before he ran the yellow light at the Magnolia Avenue 
intersection, which is in an unincorporated area. His vehicle struck a car 
pulling out of a driveway about 200 feet east of the intersection. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
STREET RACING; TRAFFIC ACCIDENTS -- ORANGE COUNTY 
</P>
